                              <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                                Sometimes, someone’s words or actions may seem trivial to them, but it scars our minds and soul forever. Harsh words once spewed and wrong actions once performed cannot be retrieved and remain part of an individual’s traumatic memory. Not only is it pivotal to control our words and actions, but it is equally essential to ensure that others’ actions do not mar our self-esteem and dignity. Bullying is one of the manifestations of such detrimental behaviour. Most of us encounter bullying in school and in our surroundings, but very few stand against it. Bullying in any form is wrong and must not be tolerated. Here are a few factors that you can take into account while confronting bullying:

                                </p>
                                <p>
                                <ul style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';"><li>●	Gain a Realistic Perspective on Self-Love </li>
